1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,378
♪ <i>Oh, tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,461 --> 00:00:08,633
["Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,717 --> 00:00:10,802
♪ <i>Fix this, oh, tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,885 --> 00:00:12,971
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:13,054 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's done</i>
<i>In the chaos of the world</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,768
- [Dmitri, in English] <i>My daughter is here.</i>
- Dad!

7
00:00:18,852 --> 00:00:22,856
[Mercado] <i>I think</i>
<i>his daughter's ex is broke.</i>

8
00:00:22,939 --> 00:00:24,607
<i>That's why he doesn't</i>
<i>want them to get back together.</i>

9
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:25,900
[Atoy chuckles softly]

10
00:00:25,984 --> 00:00:27,694
[Atoy] <i>That's why I avoid rich women, sir.</i>

11
00:00:27,777 --> 00:00:30,655
<i>Their families might</i>
<i>look down on us, right?</i>

12
00:00:30,739 --> 00:00:34,492
[Ibyang] He's an old bachelor.
That's why he's grumpy!

13
00:00:34,576 --> 00:00:38,371
[Dmitri, in English] Don't you think it's
about time that you let go of that guy

14
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:39,873
and move on?

15
00:00:39,956 --> 00:00:42,167
That man is important to Audrey.

16
00:00:42,792 --> 00:00:45,670
What if we made a mistake
with what we did before?

17
00:00:45,754 --> 00:00:48,465
[Red, in English] What's important
is that we protect our secret.

18
00:00:48,548 --> 00:00:50,592
[Vilma] <i>Why do you want to see him?</i>

19
00:00:50,675 --> 00:00:52,844
They said those were military spies.

20
00:00:52,927 --> 00:00:53,928
[Vilma] <i>Part of his plan</i>

21
00:00:54,012 --> 00:00:56,806
<i>was to get to know and win</i>
<i>the trust of the people here</i>

22
00:00:56,890 --> 00:00:58,433
<i>for their operation.</i>

23
00:00:58,516 --> 00:00:59,934
[Karla] <i>There are missing girls.</i>

24
00:01:00,018 --> 00:01:02,353
The police said they eloped.

25
00:01:02,437 --> 00:01:03,813
But the families said

26
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:06,316
they met someone on a dating app,
then disappeared?

27
00:01:06,399 --> 00:01:09,110
[Cita] <i>Atoy, Queenie is missing.</i>

28
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:10,570
They need your help.

29
00:01:10,653 --> 00:01:11,821
Huh?

30
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:13,948
PREVIOUSLY

31
00:01:14,032 --> 00:01:15,909
♪ <i>Fix this</i> ♪

32
00:01:18,703 --> 00:01:22,290
[pensive music playing]

33
00:01:22,373 --> 00:01:24,292
[Peping] I messaged Queenie

34
00:01:24,375 --> 00:01:26,586
to pick up the cassock from your shop,

35
00:01:26,669 --> 00:01:28,338
but she didn't reply.

36
00:01:28,421 --> 00:01:31,090
She's not like that.
She always replies to me.

37
00:01:31,174 --> 00:01:32,425
I called her.

38
00:01:32,509 --> 00:01:34,844
[in English] "The subscriber
cannot be reached."

39
00:01:36,304 --> 00:01:38,389
I also called her friends.

40
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,266
No one knows where she is.

41
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:42,811
They said she didn't go to school.

42
00:01:42,894 --> 00:01:45,563
[sinister music playing]

43
00:01:45,647 --> 00:01:47,106
When did you last see her?

44
00:01:47,190 --> 00:01:49,859
Our schedules don't match.

45
00:01:49,943 --> 00:01:52,529
She wakes up early to go to school.

46
00:01:52,612 --> 00:01:54,197
I get up at noon.

47
00:01:54,823 --> 00:01:57,909
[sinister music playing]

48
00:01:57,992 --> 00:02:01,454
[door hinge squeaking]

49
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:03,790
[sinister music playing]

50
00:02:03,873 --> 00:02:06,543
- [Rachel clears throat]
- [Queeni groans, inhales]

51
00:02:06,626 --> 00:02:07,669
[groans]

52
00:02:07,752 --> 00:02:10,547
[sinister music playing]

53
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,477
[sniffles]

54
00:02:26,729 --> 00:02:27,564
‪[clears throat]

55
00:02:31,568 --> 00:02:32,986
[exhales]

56
00:02:36,322 --> 00:02:37,949
[exhales, sniffles]

57
00:02:40,160 --> 00:02:41,578
[Rachel] <i>She gets a cold at night.</i>

58
00:02:41,661 --> 00:02:44,205
That's why she always applies this.

59
00:02:44,914 --> 00:02:48,710
[suspicious music playing]

60
00:03:06,519 --> 00:03:08,062
[Atoy] This bed is cold.

61
00:03:13,651 --> 00:03:15,486
And the smell of the ointment is faint.

62
00:03:16,070 --> 00:03:17,864
She didn't sleep here last night.

63
00:03:18,448 --> 00:03:21,993
My God, help us find my niece.

64
00:03:22,076 --> 00:03:24,454
Where could she have gone?

65
00:03:25,288 --> 00:03:26,915
Where's her usual hangout?

66
00:03:26,998 --> 00:03:29,167
I know she only goes to school and home.

67
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:30,668
And Bahay Kayakap.

68
00:03:30,752 --> 00:03:32,253
She works there part-time.

69
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:33,880
Bahay Kayakap?

70
00:03:38,176 --> 00:03:39,385
Where's that?

71
00:03:39,469 --> 00:03:41,554
[music fades]

72
00:03:41,638 --> 00:03:42,472
[Audrey] Uh… Hi, Dad!

73
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:45,016
[in English] I just arrived.
I'll see you at home.

74
00:03:45,099 --> 00:03:48,603
[in English] I wasn't expecting you
to be home so soon.

75
00:03:48,686 --> 00:03:52,690
But anyway,
we're all here at Martina's event.

76
00:03:52,774 --> 00:03:55,735
She mentioned this before,
the surprise project.

77
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:58,821
[in English] You mean,
her so-called non-profit thing?

78
00:03:58,905 --> 00:04:01,824
[in English] Yes.
It's a shelter for women,

79
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:03,117
Bahay Kayakap.

80
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:06,871
They have VAWC Awareness month
or something here.

81
00:04:06,955 --> 00:04:09,207
[in English] Wow. That's big of her.

82
00:04:09,290 --> 00:04:10,750
[Dmitri, in English] <i>But you know what?</i>

83
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:14,128
It's better if you come straight here.

84
00:04:14,212 --> 00:04:15,463
[in English] Check it out.

85
00:04:15,546 --> 00:04:18,091
Maybe you'd like to help
your sister-in-law.

86
00:04:18,174 --> 00:04:20,176
[in English] Okay, fine.

87
00:04:20,260 --> 00:04:21,511
[in English] Fine.
I'll see you there, Dad.

88
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:24,514
[in English] All right.
I'll see you then. Bye.

89
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:28,434
[music concludes]

90
00:04:33,189 --> 00:04:35,400
Queenie and I
started here at the same time,

91
00:04:35,483 --> 00:04:37,527
and it's been six months.

92
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:41,030
But she never misses work,
so I'm surprised that

93
00:04:41,114 --> 00:04:43,700
she's not here today,
especially with the event.

94
00:04:44,867 --> 00:04:46,327
Did you notice

95
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,454
anything unusual about her lately?

96
00:04:48,538 --> 00:04:51,291
Not with Queenie, but…

97
00:04:51,374 --> 00:04:53,584
But? But, but, what?

98
00:04:53,668 --> 00:04:55,169
I heard her with Jeff.

99
00:04:55,712 --> 00:04:57,380
He's courting Queenie.

100
00:04:57,463 --> 00:04:59,674
They argued the other day.

101
00:04:59,757 --> 00:05:03,678
He said they would be together
whether Queenie liked it or not.

102
00:05:03,761 --> 00:05:06,097
That suitor is crazy. He's forcing her.

103
00:05:06,180 --> 00:05:08,349
He really has a hot temper.

104
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:12,562
So, he might be behind
Queenie's disappearance.

105
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:14,314
Where can we find this Jeff?

106
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:16,441
He also works part-time here.

107
00:05:17,066 --> 00:05:19,485
[music concludes]

108
00:05:19,569 --> 00:05:20,445
[host] Ladies and gentlemen,

109
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:22,488
please give another round of applause

110
00:05:22,572 --> 00:05:24,657
for Ms. Tala Gatchalian!

111
00:05:24,741 --> 00:05:25,783
[audience applauds]

112
00:05:25,867 --> 00:05:29,329
♪ <i>Close your mouth</i> ♪

113
00:05:29,412 --> 00:05:36,210
♪ <i>Shut your mind to endless dreams</i> ♪

114
00:05:37,336 --> 00:05:42,592
♪ <i>Even if it goes in circles</i> ♪

115
00:05:42,675 --> 00:05:49,599
♪ <i>Life will strike, it has an end</i> ♪

116
00:05:49,682 --> 00:05:55,855
♪ <i>Even if you can't see it</i>
<i>The light will come</i> ♪

117
00:05:55,938 --> 00:06:01,444
♪ <i>The sun will rise</i> ♪

118
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:08,034
♪ <i>Instill it in your mind</i>
<i>That you're not just</i> ♪

119
00:06:08,868 --> 00:06:12,080
♪ <i>Stuck here</i> ♪

120
00:06:12,705 --> 00:06:15,458
♪ <i>Oh, fight</i> ♪

121
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:18,169
♪ <i>Oh, shout it out</i> ♪

122
00:06:18,252 --> 00:06:24,425
♪ <i>Your weakness is also your strength</i> ♪

123
00:06:24,509 --> 00:06:28,930
♪ <i>Because the future</i> ♪

124
00:06:29,013 --> 00:06:33,226
♪ <i>Is in your hands…</i> ♪

125
00:06:33,309 --> 00:06:38,064
[sauve music playing]

126
00:07:01,337 --> 00:07:02,713
[music concludes]

127
00:07:02,797 --> 00:07:07,552
[vocalizing]

128
00:07:07,635 --> 00:07:08,469
♪ <i>Baby</i> ♪

129
00:07:08,553 --> 00:07:09,595
[audience applauds]

130
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:10,930
That's him!

131
00:07:11,931 --> 00:07:14,058
[exhilarating music playing]

132
00:07:15,226 --> 00:07:16,811
[Dmitri] Hey, Audrey!

133
00:07:16,894 --> 00:07:18,563
- [in English] You're here.
- [in English] Hi, Dad.

134
00:07:18,646 --> 00:07:23,651
[tense music playing]

135
00:07:23,734 --> 00:07:25,236
Where is he?

136
00:07:26,904 --> 00:07:29,240
Who? Who are you looking for?

137
00:07:29,323 --> 00:07:31,909
- [tense music playing]
- [Audrey gasping]

138
00:07:34,954 --> 00:07:39,250
Nothing. Uh… I thought I saw something.

139
00:07:41,002 --> 00:07:42,462
[in English] Never mind.

140
00:07:43,129 --> 00:07:44,589
Where are the two--

141
00:07:45,715 --> 00:07:47,175
Martina, Red.

142
00:07:48,092 --> 00:07:49,469
[in English] Your sister is here.

143
00:07:49,552 --> 00:07:51,179
[in English] Oh! Oh, hi!

144
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:53,848
- [in English] Hi, Audrey!
- [in English] Ah, come on down.

145
00:07:58,811 --> 00:07:59,812
[in English] Yes.

146
00:07:59,896 --> 00:08:01,105
[Karla] You bastard!

147
00:08:01,189 --> 00:08:02,356
[energetic music playing]

148
00:08:02,440 --> 00:08:04,692
[grunting and groaning]

149
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:06,486
- [bone snaps]
- [grunts]

150
00:08:06,569 --> 00:08:10,031
[tense music playing]

151
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:11,073
[Jeff] Ouch.

152
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:13,075
- [Atoy] Karla.
- [Gavin, in English] What's going on here?

153
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:17,580
Sir, she attacked me!

154
00:08:17,663 --> 00:08:18,956
I don't even know her.

155
00:08:19,040 --> 00:08:21,083
[sinister music playing]

156
00:08:21,167 --> 00:08:22,793
What are you doing here?

157
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:25,755
[in English] My mom runs this shelter.

158
00:08:25,838 --> 00:08:28,174
You? What are you guys doing here?

159
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:29,842
[music intensifies slightly]

160
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:31,636
We just need to talk to him.

161
00:08:31,719 --> 00:08:35,306
[music intensifies]

162
00:08:40,061 --> 00:08:41,145
Are you sure you're okay?

163
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:43,397
- [in English] I'll get you water.
- No need!

164
00:08:43,481 --> 00:08:45,274
I wasn't even hit.

165
00:08:46,150 --> 00:08:48,986
And if that ever happens,
my revenge will be much worse.

166
00:08:49,862 --> 00:08:51,239
[in English] That's not gonna happen.

167
00:08:51,322 --> 00:08:53,199
[in English] Not on my watch.

168
00:08:53,282 --> 00:08:55,326
[Jeff] I don't know anything
about that, man.

169
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:59,247
Queenie rejected me,
so we don't talk anymore.

170
00:09:00,122 --> 00:09:02,583
So, you just accepted it?

171
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:04,752
- Just like that? You're fine with that?
- [Jeff scoffs]

172
00:09:05,378 --> 00:09:08,589
I wasn't even serious about courting her,

173
00:09:08,673 --> 00:09:10,341
so it's okay.

174
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,636
Come on. I still have work.

175
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,013
Wait!

176
00:09:16,097 --> 00:09:19,225
[pensive music playing]

177
00:09:20,434 --> 00:09:23,229
Not serious, but you have
a couple's keychain?

178
00:09:24,230 --> 00:09:26,857
I saw the other pair.

179
00:09:26,941 --> 00:09:27,984
[music intensifies]

180
00:09:28,067 --> 00:09:30,027
[Atoy] <i>Right there in Queenie's room.</i>

181
00:09:30,111 --> 00:09:31,362
On her desk.

182
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:33,864
[keys jingling]

183
00:09:35,157 --> 00:09:36,367
She kept it?

184
00:09:38,536 --> 00:09:39,954
But she didn't use it.

185
00:09:40,830 --> 00:09:44,333
I told her, if she used it,

186
00:09:44,417 --> 00:09:46,002
that would mean we're together.

187
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:48,170
[music fades]

188
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:53,217
[mysterious music playing]

189
00:09:57,597 --> 00:09:59,932
Queenie! I brought--

190
00:10:02,935 --> 00:10:04,478
Who are you talking to?

191
00:10:04,562 --> 00:10:05,855
Jeff.

192
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:09,775
- No one. No one.
- Let me see!

193
00:10:09,859 --> 00:10:11,027
No one-- Jeff!

194
00:10:11,110 --> 00:10:12,486
- Jeff, what?!
- Who is it?!

195
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,031
Jeff, it's my boyfriend!

196
00:10:15,740 --> 00:10:16,949
What boyfriend?!

197
00:10:17,742 --> 00:10:19,910
You told me you weren't ready!

198
00:10:20,494 --> 00:10:24,123
I only said that because
you won't accept my rejection.

199
00:10:24,206 --> 00:10:26,542
Who is that, huh? Where did you meet him?

200
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:28,878
Why doesn't he even pick you up here?

201
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:31,339
- Jeff, it's none of your business.
- Where?!

202
00:10:31,422 --> 00:10:32,840
On MatchTayo?!

203
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:35,509
Jeff, please. It's none of your business.

204
00:10:35,593 --> 00:10:37,803
What?! I've been courting you
for a long time!

205
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:42,141
Then you dumped me for someone
you met on a dating app?!

206
00:10:42,224 --> 00:10:43,225
[in English] Jeff, please.

207
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:44,393
- Just accept it--
- No!

208
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:45,394
Jeff!

209
00:10:46,270 --> 00:10:48,439
I've put so much effort into you, Queenie!

210
00:10:48,522 --> 00:10:49,440
[in English] Jeff, please.

211
00:10:49,523 --> 00:10:51,525
- Calm down first. Jeff.
- I won't allow

212
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:53,152
- Jeff, it hurts.
- all of that to go to waste!

213
00:10:53,235 --> 00:10:55,112
You're hurting me. Jeff, please!

214
00:10:55,196 --> 00:10:56,530
- You're hurting me!
- I don't care.

215
00:10:56,614 --> 00:10:58,741
- We'll still be together!
- Jeff, stop it.

216
00:10:58,824 --> 00:11:00,326
- Whether you like it or not.
- Please, please, please!

217
00:11:00,409 --> 00:11:02,370
- Jeff, stop it!
- We'll still be together!

218
00:11:02,453 --> 00:11:04,580
Jeff, stop it! What are you doing?

219
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:05,748
Jeff! [gasps]

220
00:11:05,831 --> 00:11:07,375
[man] That's enough.

221
00:11:07,458 --> 00:11:12,213
[pensive music playing]

222
00:11:12,922 --> 00:11:15,299
I only said that because I was upset.

223
00:11:16,342 --> 00:11:18,135
I don't hurt women.

224
00:11:18,219 --> 00:11:19,470
- I can't do that.
- What do you mean you can't?

225
00:11:20,137 --> 00:11:22,098
You almost hit me, right?

226
00:11:22,807 --> 00:11:24,141
Does that look like a woman's face?

227
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:25,768
- Hey, that's foul!
- Oop, oop. That's enough.

228
00:11:25,851 --> 00:11:26,977
That's enough, that's enough.

229
00:11:27,061 --> 00:11:28,979
[suspicious music playing]

230
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,523
Where were you the other night?

231
00:11:31,816 --> 00:11:34,110
We stayed up two nights at the shelter.

232
00:11:35,611 --> 00:11:39,115
We did nothing but prepare
all night for today's event.

233
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:42,410
Ask my companions.

234
00:11:42,493 --> 00:11:44,745
I was never out of their sight.

235
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:54,130
[music fades]

236
00:11:55,881 --> 00:11:57,007
[in English] Hey, sis!

237
00:11:58,634 --> 00:12:01,053
[in English] How did
your soul-searching go?

238
00:12:01,137 --> 00:12:04,598
It was fine. Peaceful.

239
00:12:04,682 --> 00:12:06,350
[in English] I was able to relax.

240
00:12:06,434 --> 00:12:09,061
You went soul-searching
here in the Philippines.

241
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:12,440
Isn't that what you were
already doing in the States?

242
00:12:13,274 --> 00:12:15,317
[in English] I mean, um…

243
00:12:15,401 --> 00:12:17,194
[mysterious music playing]

244
00:12:17,278 --> 00:12:19,113
[in English] Don't tell me
it's because of a man.

245
00:12:22,324 --> 00:12:25,619
[in English] Martina,
what are you getting at?

246
00:12:25,703 --> 00:12:26,912
[in English] Nothing, Dad.

247
00:12:26,996 --> 00:12:28,706
[in English] I'm just saying that Audrey

248
00:12:28,789 --> 00:12:30,833
could possibly do something
a little bit more, you know,

249
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:32,668
worthwhile with her time.

250
00:12:32,751 --> 00:12:34,211
Like me, right?

251
00:12:34,295 --> 00:12:37,256
I built this shelter to help other people.

252
00:12:38,299 --> 00:12:42,511
[in English] And I applaud you
for your charity, Martina.

253
00:12:42,595 --> 00:12:45,848
But, since it looks like
you've got this covered,

254
00:12:45,931 --> 00:12:48,684
I'll just help Big Brother
with the company,

255
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:52,396
so someone's watching over him too.

256
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,564
Right?

257
00:12:54,356 --> 00:12:55,566
What are you implying?

258
00:12:55,649 --> 00:12:57,318
What am I, ten years old?

259
00:12:59,236 --> 00:13:00,946
I don't know, brother.

260
00:13:01,030 --> 00:13:02,239
[in English] You tell me.

261
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,825
Since Dad left,

262
00:13:04,909 --> 00:13:06,869
have you heard of any problems
in the company?

263
00:13:06,952 --> 00:13:08,746
[Dmitri, in English] Hey, hey! Stop it.

264
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:11,957
[in English] Looks like I need a refill.

265
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:14,376
[in English] Excuse me.

266
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:18,923
[suspicious music playing]

267
00:13:23,886 --> 00:13:25,596
[music fades]

268
00:13:27,181 --> 00:13:31,185
[sinister music playing]

269
00:13:38,317 --> 00:13:39,151
‪[music intensifies]

270
00:13:48,452 --> 00:13:49,912
[music concludes]

271
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:51,664
[in English] Hello, Father?

272
00:13:51,747 --> 00:13:53,832
Wh-- What?

273
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,626
Go ahead to the car.

274
00:13:55,709 --> 00:13:57,127
I'll drive, Big Brother.

275
00:13:59,547 --> 00:14:01,674
Wait, Father. Ah, here.

276
00:14:01,757 --> 00:14:02,591
Hello, hello?

277
00:14:03,634 --> 00:14:04,468
That?

278
00:14:05,844 --> 00:14:08,722
Do you hear me now? Okay.

279
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:12,101
Ah, Father, let's just meet
at Queenie's house.

280
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:13,519
I'm on my way there now.

281
00:14:15,896 --> 00:14:16,855
[in English] Okay, Father.

282
00:14:16,939 --> 00:14:19,066
[ominous music playing]

283
00:14:19,859 --> 00:14:20,776
[Red] Where's my lighter?

284
00:14:24,738 --> 00:14:26,532
[Mongki] Oh, I don't know.
It's not with me.

285
00:14:26,615 --> 00:14:28,200
- It's with you!
- It's not!

286
00:14:28,284 --> 00:14:30,744
Get some matches!

287
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:33,372
Idiot.

288
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:36,834
[music turns unsettling]

289
00:14:46,594 --> 00:14:47,595
[swishes softly]

290
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:53,100
[music fades]

291
00:14:57,479 --> 00:14:59,064
[gun cocks]

292
00:14:59,148 --> 00:15:00,441
[tense music playing]

293
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,620
Red! Son!

294
00:15:12,703 --> 00:15:14,496
- [in English] There you are!
- Yes. Yes, ma'am?

295
00:15:14,580 --> 00:15:15,748
[in English] Where's Martina?

296
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:17,374
[in English] Oh, uh, she's inside.

297
00:15:18,083 --> 00:15:20,377
Come with me. Let's go.

298
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:22,630
- My feet hurt already.
- [in English] Okay, no problem.

299
00:15:23,380 --> 00:15:26,050
[tense music playing]

300
00:15:36,852 --> 00:15:39,188
[music fades]

301
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:42,775
Oh? What happened to you, brother?

302
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:43,692
Let's go.

303
00:15:43,776 --> 00:15:46,028
The guy I fought with
at Endless Nights is here.

304
00:15:46,111 --> 00:15:47,988
What's he doing here?

305
00:15:48,072 --> 00:15:50,115
Brother, could there be
an underground fight ring inside?

306
00:15:50,199 --> 00:15:51,951
I don't know.

307
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:55,329
But every time I see him, it feels like
something illegal is happening.

308
00:15:56,288 --> 00:15:57,831
But that's not
our concern anymore. Let's go.

309
00:15:57,915 --> 00:15:59,667
[car engine starts]

310
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:04,088
[tense music playing]

311
00:16:08,092 --> 00:16:09,301
Brother Kurt…

312
00:16:09,385 --> 00:16:11,428
- [music fades]
- [indistinct]

313
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:12,972
Write it down first.

314
00:16:13,055 --> 00:16:15,391
Hmm. All right. But you pay later, ah!

315
00:16:15,474 --> 00:16:17,851
Or else, I will report you to Atoy.

316
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:26,193
If I report him, it's you, huh.

317
00:16:26,276 --> 00:16:27,861
- [overlapping chatter]
- Mmm?

318
00:16:27,945 --> 00:16:29,071
Oh! Wait, wait, wait!

319
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:30,823
[lively chatter in distance]

320
00:16:30,906 --> 00:16:33,784
Manong doesn't even recognize me anymore.

321
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:35,494
[broom swishing]

322
00:16:37,871 --> 00:16:42,626
Well, that person had a glow-up too.

323
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:46,505
Right? She doesn't snivel anymore.
She's prettier now!

324
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:48,882
[chuckles softly] Her skin got smoother!

325
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,217
Hey! [chuckles softly]

326
00:16:50,300 --> 00:16:53,429
Wow. True Filipino beauty indeed!

327
00:16:53,512 --> 00:16:54,805
[playful music playing]

328
00:16:54,888 --> 00:16:57,433
Mmm, you're too hung up on yourself.

329
00:16:58,142 --> 00:16:59,226
That's enough.

330
00:17:00,436 --> 00:17:02,312
Oh, c'mon! My turn!

331
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:03,564
- [man 1] You're so selfish.
- [man 2] My turn!

332
00:17:03,647 --> 00:17:05,190
[man 1] I've been hungry for a while!

333
00:17:05,274 --> 00:17:08,068
- Hey, Emerson!
- Hmm?

334
00:17:08,152 --> 00:17:09,528
Who are you looking at?

335
00:17:09,611 --> 00:17:12,865
[crickets chirping]

336
00:17:14,491 --> 00:17:16,035
[man 2] That's enough,
that's enough! Slowly.

337
00:17:19,997 --> 00:17:21,290
Hey.

338
00:17:21,373 --> 00:17:22,332
[mellow music playing]

339
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,250
Uh…

340
00:17:24,501 --> 00:17:25,919
Hi, Tonet!

341
00:17:26,003 --> 00:17:27,129
Hi!

342
00:17:27,212 --> 00:17:28,881
[music fades]

343
00:17:28,964 --> 00:17:30,549
[broom swishing]

344
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:32,092
[quirky music playing]

345
00:17:32,176 --> 00:17:33,135
You know,

346
00:17:34,178 --> 00:17:36,638
Atoy's new assistant
is really a babe, right?

347
00:17:38,057 --> 00:17:39,683
Just snobbish.

348
00:17:41,268 --> 00:17:44,646
But it's okay.
She'll fall for me eventually.

349
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,065
[chuckles] Almost there, Captain.

350
00:17:46,148 --> 00:17:47,649
- You can do it, Captain.
- Just a little more push.

351
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,693
[music fades]

352
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,489
[broom swishing]

353
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:56,575
[suspicious music playing]

354
00:18:01,747 --> 00:18:03,207
She doesn't seem snobbish.

355
00:18:03,916 --> 00:18:05,250
Maybe she just doesn't like you.

356
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:06,794
Son of a--

357
00:18:06,877 --> 00:18:08,670
Me? Not her type?

358
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:11,757
Then who?

359
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,301
Raul?

360
00:18:14,968 --> 00:18:16,095
- This one?
- Oh.

361
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,349
He's handsome too.

362
00:18:20,432 --> 00:18:22,142
[laughs]

363
00:18:23,685 --> 00:18:25,270
You?

364
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:26,897
You've got some nerve, Emerson.

365
00:18:26,980 --> 00:18:29,650
Whoa! Munggo, give him some coffee.

366
00:18:29,733 --> 00:18:31,443
Yes, a liter!

367
00:18:31,527 --> 00:18:32,778
With that face?

368
00:18:32,861 --> 00:18:33,737
Wake up!

369
00:18:33,821 --> 00:18:34,863
[chuckles]

370
00:18:34,947 --> 00:18:36,657
[music fades]

371
00:18:37,866 --> 00:18:40,494
[Atoy] I talked to her colleagues
at the shelter.

372
00:18:40,577 --> 00:18:43,539
They said they prepared
all night for the event.

373
00:18:44,748 --> 00:18:46,875
Jeff's excuse seems solid.

374
00:18:48,168 --> 00:18:50,629
The police already issued an alert.

375
00:18:50,712 --> 00:18:52,047
But they told us maybe

376
00:18:52,131 --> 00:18:55,134
Queenie just eloped.

377
00:18:55,217 --> 00:18:56,343
She wouldn't do that, Atoy.

378
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,929
Jeff said she had

379
00:18:59,012 --> 00:19:00,305
a boyfriend.

380
00:19:00,889 --> 00:19:02,683
Someone she met on a dating app.

381
00:19:03,642 --> 00:19:06,478
Do you know anything about this?

382
00:19:07,146 --> 00:19:10,274
We don't have our regular
sibling bonding anymore.

383
00:19:10,941 --> 00:19:14,736
I got promoted,
so I became busier at work.

384
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:17,197
We hardly talk.

385
00:19:17,281 --> 00:19:19,992
[suspicious music playing]

386
00:19:20,075 --> 00:19:20,993
Rachel.

387
00:19:21,076 --> 00:19:22,244
[music fades]

388
00:19:22,828 --> 00:19:25,956
Since our parents separated

389
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:27,666
and had other families,

390
00:19:29,334 --> 00:19:32,045
we promised each other as siblings
never to abandon one another.

391
00:19:32,129 --> 00:19:34,006
[tense music playing]

392
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:35,507
But I didn't fulfill that.

393
00:19:35,591 --> 00:19:37,801
I still neglected her.

394
00:19:37,885 --> 00:19:40,137
[tense music playing]

395
00:19:40,220 --> 00:19:41,847
[sobs]

396
00:19:54,026 --> 00:19:56,528
So… who's more handsome between you two?

397
00:19:56,612 --> 00:19:58,155
- Do you even have to ask?
- Hmm.

398
00:19:58,238 --> 00:19:59,781
- See? See?
- Mmm.

399
00:19:59,865 --> 00:20:02,534
Ah-- Oh, oh, oh, oh!

400
00:20:02,618 --> 00:20:03,619
[quirky music playing]

401
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:05,412
From any angle, bro.

402
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:07,164
Oh, oh.

403
00:20:07,247 --> 00:20:08,916
[in English] All right,
all right, all right.

404
00:20:08,999 --> 00:20:10,792
[music fades]

405
00:20:14,796 --> 00:20:18,342
[whimsical music playing]

406
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:23,472
[Tonet] Oh, oh! Oh, sorry.

407
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:24,640
[panting]

408
00:20:25,641 --> 00:20:27,017
What happened to you?

409
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:29,561
[chuckles]

410
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:30,979
[in English] What was that?

411
00:20:31,063 --> 00:20:32,689
[giggles]

412
00:20:32,773 --> 00:20:33,982
[in English] What's that?

413
00:20:34,066 --> 00:20:35,984
[in English] What's that? Hmm?

414
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:39,238
[in English] Is it me, or is it me? Hmm?

415
00:20:40,572 --> 00:20:41,990
[in English] Correct me if I'm wrong, huh?

416
00:20:42,074 --> 00:20:44,284
[in English] Is it me? [smirks]

417
00:20:52,834 --> 00:20:54,962
[in English] Oh, come on.

418
00:20:56,088 --> 00:20:57,464
[in English] What's that?

419
00:20:57,547 --> 00:20:58,674
[music fades]

420
00:20:58,757 --> 00:20:59,925
Hmm.

421
00:21:00,801 --> 00:21:03,553
[quirky music playing]

422
00:21:10,435 --> 00:21:11,979
Hmm.

423
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:14,481
Got you!

424
00:21:14,564 --> 00:21:15,524
[quirky sting]

425
00:21:15,607 --> 00:21:17,526
[in English] Who would have thought?

426
00:21:17,609 --> 00:21:20,070
[in English] Hmm? Not me. Not me.

427
00:21:20,153 --> 00:21:22,155
[in English] Not you? [giggles]

428
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:24,700
[in English] Kurt, where's that, uh,

429
00:21:24,783 --> 00:21:26,326
special coffee of yours?

430
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:29,162
- [overlapping chatter]
- Give me some of your special coffee.

431
00:21:29,246 --> 00:21:30,747
- [Kurt] Yes, I'll try that.
- [in English] But no sugar.

432
00:21:30,831 --> 00:21:32,291
[in English] I'm sweet enough.

433
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,418
[giggles]

434
00:21:35,210 --> 00:21:37,671
[indistinct chattering]

435
00:21:37,754 --> 00:21:39,214
[music fades]

436
00:21:39,298 --> 00:21:41,675
[pensive music playing]

437
00:21:41,758 --> 00:21:44,344
Are you hiding from Emerson?

438
00:21:45,387 --> 00:21:47,264
Why would I hide from him?

439
00:21:47,347 --> 00:21:48,765
Who is he anyway?

440
00:21:48,849 --> 00:21:51,143
Well, your crush!

441
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:53,729
Huh? Ew! Yuck!

442
00:21:53,812 --> 00:21:55,522
What crush? No way!

443
00:21:56,106 --> 00:21:57,482
Oh my!

444
00:21:57,566 --> 00:22:00,694
Stop denying. It's obvious.

445
00:22:00,777 --> 00:22:02,154
You can't even look him
straight in the eye

446
00:22:02,237 --> 00:22:04,406
because you're so giddy!

447
00:22:05,073 --> 00:22:06,575
Are you okay? What are you talking about?

448
00:22:06,658 --> 00:22:08,160
Like, no.

449
00:22:08,243 --> 00:22:09,786
Do you want me to set you up?

450
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:11,455
I'm a good matchmaker.

451
00:22:11,538 --> 00:22:14,166
I worked as a cupid at the fair before.

452
00:22:14,249 --> 00:22:15,876
- [in English] No, thanks!
- Hmm.

453
00:22:15,959 --> 00:22:18,795
And stop saying that Emerson is my crush.

454
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,672
- Gross!
- Hey, Tonet!

455
00:22:20,756 --> 00:22:21,673
Don't say that!

456
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:24,134
Even if Emerson isn't that handsome,

457
00:22:24,217 --> 00:22:26,136
it's not right to call him gross!

458
00:22:27,012 --> 00:22:30,265
Miss Cita, you really
don't understand me, as in!

459
00:22:30,891 --> 00:22:33,351
[in Visayan] You do whatever you like!

460
00:22:33,435 --> 00:22:35,020
What did she say?

461
00:22:35,103 --> 00:22:38,023
[chuckles] I don't know. Still denying it.

462
00:22:38,106 --> 00:22:40,942
[quirky music playing]

463
00:22:41,026 --> 00:22:43,445
[in English] I'm really tired.
I'm gonna go to bed, Dad.

464
00:22:43,528 --> 00:22:45,655
- [in English] Good night.
- [in English] Good night.

465
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:48,825
[crickets chirping]

466
00:22:49,951 --> 00:22:50,911
Martina.

467
00:22:53,080 --> 00:22:54,790
What's your problem with Audrey?

468
00:22:55,457 --> 00:22:57,209
- Dad--
- You reminded her about

469
00:22:57,292 --> 00:22:58,752
the man she's looking for.

470
00:22:58,835 --> 00:23:00,587
[in English] How insensitive of you?

471
00:23:00,670 --> 00:23:02,464
[in English] Dad, why are you
attacking my wife?

472
00:23:02,547 --> 00:23:04,966
She just reiterated
our problem with Audrey.

473
00:23:05,050 --> 00:23:06,551
[mysterious music playing]

474
00:23:06,635 --> 00:23:09,346
Dad, I just told her that
what she's doing is pointless

475
00:23:09,429 --> 00:23:11,515
and pushed her in the right direction.

476
00:23:11,598 --> 00:23:12,891
I had no bad intentions, Dad.

477
00:23:12,974 --> 00:23:14,851
[in English] You know me.
I'm on your side!

478
00:23:15,602 --> 00:23:17,521
[in English] This is all your fault!

479
00:23:17,604 --> 00:23:19,314
Both of you!

480
00:23:19,397 --> 00:23:21,149
[mysterious music playing]

481
00:23:21,233 --> 00:23:22,442
How is it our fault?

482
00:23:23,110 --> 00:23:24,528
If I hadn't listened to you,

483
00:23:25,112 --> 00:23:27,572
we wouldn't be hiding
anything from Audrey!

484
00:23:29,366 --> 00:23:32,494
[in English] But, Dad, that decision

485
00:23:32,577 --> 00:23:35,080
is why you and Audrey fixed
your relationship in the first place.

486
00:23:35,163 --> 00:23:38,625
Look, your daughter takes care of you
and loves you so much now.

487
00:23:39,709 --> 00:23:42,379
Your relationship healed
because of what we did.

488
00:23:42,462 --> 00:23:44,506
[in English] But this is not real healing,

489
00:23:45,423 --> 00:23:49,136
if we are keeping something
really important from her!

490
00:23:49,219 --> 00:23:52,180
And I'm dreading the day the wound opens

491
00:23:52,264 --> 00:23:53,890
and everything is revealed!

492
00:23:54,474 --> 00:23:56,268
But that will never happen, right?

493
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:58,478
Because only the three of us know…

494
00:24:00,063 --> 00:24:01,773
and no one will tell her.

495
00:24:02,941 --> 00:24:04,109
[in English] Right, Dad?

496
00:24:04,192 --> 00:24:08,655
[suspicious music playing]

497
00:24:17,038 --> 00:24:17,998
Brother Atoy,

498
00:24:18,915 --> 00:24:21,334
do you remember the news
I showed you before?

499
00:24:22,169 --> 00:24:24,546
About the women who dated on MatchTayo,

500
00:24:24,629 --> 00:24:25,755
then suddenly disappeared?

501
00:24:26,965 --> 00:24:28,675
What if that's what happened to Queenie?

502
00:24:30,010 --> 00:24:31,428
It's possible.

503
00:24:31,511 --> 00:24:32,846
[pensive music playing]

504
00:24:32,929 --> 00:24:35,307
But you know her better.

505
00:24:35,390 --> 00:24:36,391
[pensive music playing]

506
00:24:36,474 --> 00:24:39,436
Do you think she's the type
to make a profile

507
00:24:40,562 --> 00:24:43,273
and post and upload it on that website?

508
00:24:43,940 --> 00:24:45,192
Maybe.

509
00:24:45,275 --> 00:24:48,904
Everyone here expects her
to be perfect because…

510
00:24:49,654 --> 00:24:51,615
her uncle is Father Peping.

511
00:24:52,199 --> 00:24:53,867
But what if she just
wanted someone to talk to

512
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:55,952
who doesn't know her?

513
00:24:56,036 --> 00:24:58,038
So, there are no expectations.

514
00:24:58,622 --> 00:24:59,915
Is that so?

515
00:24:59,998 --> 00:25:01,791
Maybe I should make
a profile on MatchTayo.

516
00:25:01,875 --> 00:25:03,084
Just to see if Queenie is there.

517
00:25:03,168 --> 00:25:04,878
Don't! You--

518
00:25:04,961 --> 00:25:06,880
You were already
forbidden to do so, right?

519
00:25:06,963 --> 00:25:09,799
You can't. You might end up
a victim yourself.

520
00:25:09,883 --> 00:25:11,009
No way!

521
00:25:11,092 --> 00:25:12,928
I have presence of mind.

522
00:25:13,011 --> 00:25:15,263
I just want to help find Queenie.

523
00:25:16,640 --> 00:25:19,976
I'll search. But then Cita
might get mad at me again.

524
00:25:20,060 --> 00:25:21,603
Don't!

525
00:25:21,686 --> 00:25:22,854
Here's what we'll do.

526
00:25:23,563 --> 00:25:26,274
Just give me all the names of the victims.

527
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:27,525
[tense music playing]

528
00:25:27,609 --> 00:25:28,610
I'll take care of it.

529
00:25:29,486 --> 00:25:31,154
I'll find a way.

530
00:25:33,823 --> 00:25:35,867
[electronic blipping]

531
00:25:35,951 --> 00:25:39,746
[tense music playing]

532
00:25:42,666 --> 00:25:43,917
[music fades]

533
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:45,961
Whose names are these?

534
00:25:46,044 --> 00:25:47,295
[Atoy] Names of the victims.

535
00:25:48,004 --> 00:25:49,673
Names of the missing women.

536
00:25:49,756 --> 00:25:54,010
[Kate] She told me she was going
to meet a man at a bar.

537
00:25:54,094 --> 00:25:56,137
<i>After that, nothing.</i>

538
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:57,430
<i>She never came home.</i>

539
00:25:57,514 --> 00:25:58,848
Is that San Antonio?

540
00:25:58,932 --> 00:26:00,350
Where did you get this?

541
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:02,602
<i>From Barangay Tabang-Lupa, in Baclaran.</i>

542
00:26:02,686 --> 00:26:03,436
UP NEXT

543
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:04,729
[Gavin, in English] I'll take you.

544
00:26:04,813 --> 00:26:06,731
My friends and I play ball in that area.

545
00:26:06,815 --> 00:26:08,149
[in English] Okay.

546
00:26:08,233 --> 00:26:09,776
What happened to that girl?

547
00:26:09,859 --> 00:26:13,363
[Atoy] I won't stop
until she's returned to you.

548
00:26:14,114 --> 00:26:17,200
[Peping] I'll get sick from this,
oh, with what's happening…

549
00:26:17,284 --> 00:26:18,827
I don't know what's with that child.

550
00:26:18,910 --> 00:26:21,579
[music intensifies]

551
00:26:21,663 --> 00:26:24,457
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
